<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06172266 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06172266 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Photo; PHOTO:; Rick McCawley --; Knight-Ridder; News Service; WANNA-BE -- &quot;Iwas kind of bored,&quot; Margo Mankes says of her experience with the Girl Scouts.A hearing will be held Friday on her bid to join the Cub Scouts.  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  FEMALE; JUVENILE; LAWSUIT; MALE; CLUB  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  Eight-year-old Margo Mankes didn't find the Girl Scouts challenging. So she'schallenging the Cub Scouts for entry into the all-male club.;    &quot;There werearts and crafts, and sometimes we had to make little puppets,&quot; thethird-grader said of her experience with the Girl Scouts. &quot;I was kind ofbored.&quot;  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  General News  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  REJECTED GIRL TEACHES SCOUTS TO BE PREPARED-- FOR LAWSUIT  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Margo's attorney, Mark Rubin, sued the organization in federal courtTuesday, charging sexual discrimination. Rubin argues that the Boy Scouts ofAmerica is not a private organization because it was given federal recognitionby Congress in 1916.;    A hearing will be held Friday to determine whetherMargo can attend summer Cub Scouts camp, which begins Monday.;    &quot;Keepinggirls out of the Boy Scouts deprives them of the opportunity to get thecompanionship and the competition that they need in order to be able toprepare themselves for the future,&quot; Rubin said.;    Margo is believed to bethe first girl to challenge the Cub Scouts in court for the right to join,said Blake Lewis, a spokesman for the Dallas-based Boy Scouts of America.;   Girls have never been allowed in the 81-year-old Boy Scouts or the Cub Scouts,a group for younger boys. The Cub Scouts group is more than 60 years old.Exploring, a separate Boy Scouts program for teen-agers, does admit youngwomen.;    &quot;Our feeling is that the Cub Scouts and the Boy Scouts werespecifically designed to meet the needs for young boys. And the needs foryoung boys are very different from young girls,&quot; Lewis said.;    Local CubScout Pack 350 let Margo join in January and she purchased her uniform, capand yellow kerchief. But the Boy Scouts of America sent her a letter the nextmonth, saying no girls were allowed.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Miami  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910620  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Thursday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6C  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  332  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Thursday June 20, 199100172266,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>